evidence: The WReTaMo RHEA has a bodycentered cubic (BCC) structure with a maximal compressive strength of 1140 MPa and Vickers microhardness of 654 HV at room temperature. The alloy displays a strong resistance to high-temperature softening, showing the high maximal compressive strength of 244 MPa at 1600 C. At 1600 C, the sample shows continuous strengthening without peak stress until the final testing point at strain of 25%.
Then, the hardness increases rapidly to a high value of 723 HV as the annealing temperature rises to 2200 C.

A promising WReTaMo RHEA with high strength at 1600 C was fabricated by vacuum arc melting. The alloy displayed strong resistance to high-temperature softening, with a high maximal compressive strength of 244 MPa at 1600 C.
